I think using std::any_of here would be cleaner:

auto processReq = std::any_of(ffdcFiles.begin(), ffdcFiles.end(), [] (const auto& file)
{
  return file.format == custom && file.subType == sbeFFDCSubType;
});

how about if pelFFDC() only returned the new SBE FFDCFiles?  Then you could just just call insert() on ffdcFiles to add them:
const auto& sbeFFDCFiles = sbeFfdc.getSbeFFDC(); //return  a const reference
ffdcFiles.insert(ffdcFiles.end(), sbeFFDCFiles.begin(), sbeFFDCFiles.end());

